# GSS Log (.glog) Files

`.glog` files are inter-process messaging (IPM) logs generated by GSSMenu and GSSXBar components.

## Filename Pattern
`<pid>--<type>--<AppName>[!C<CompanyCode>][!U<Username>][!N<timestamp>]--<seq>.glog`

Example: `1060--4--GSSMenu[!CPLA][!USUPERVSR][!N260523072858]--1.glog`

## Log Entry Format
```
<level>\\\<timestamp>\\\<code>\\\<message>{&}{&}<method>{&}<class>{&}<line>{&}||
```
- **Level**: 10=config, 20=metadata, 30=runtime entry
- **Code**: 100=warning, 200=info
- **Delimiters**: `\\\` separates fields, `{&}{&}` separates message from source location

## Contents
- IPM message parsing between menu and child processes (OCTSRS.NET.EXE)
- Process registration/unregistration for script execution
- SQL queries (CRM reminders, company options)
- Script lifecycle: launch, title updates, process exit

## These Are Read-Only
Diagnostic logs only. Useful for debugging inter-process communication issues. Very noisy (~1MB per session).
